Liana in the crown of tropical trees, when lightning strikes, drains electric current into the ground and burns out at the same time, but protects the tree like a lightning rod [8]. The Caucasus Mountains is a mountain system located in Eurasia between the Black and Caspian Seas. The etymology of the name has not been established [1]. It is divided into two mountain systems: the Greater Caucasus and the Lesser Caucasus. The Caucasus is often divided into the North Caucasus and Transcaucasia, the border between which is drawn along the Main, or Watershed, ridge of the Greater Caucasus, which occupies a central position in the mountain system.